# Git commit workflow (DCapple)

When shipping work that spans multiple areas, **commit in logical slices** so each commit is one story (for example: database + model; then services; then HTTP + views; then legal copy only).

**Patterns that work well:** migration with model changes in the same commit; pair `routes/web.php` changes with the controller and views they register; keep “docs only” or “copy only” commits separate from code.

**One-line subject** in imperative mood (`feat(orders): add Paystack refund on failed delivery`), then a blank line and bullets for non-obvious details if needed.
